title: 10 Euro Cent (2nd map)

composition.text: Nordic gold (89% Copper, 5% Aluminium, 5% Zinc, 1% Tin)

obverse.description: The Sower walking left surrounded by rays, lines, and the 12 stars of the European Union
obverse.lettering: RF 2011 L. JORIO d'ap. O. ROTY
obverse.unabridged_legend: Republique Française 2011 Laurent Jorio d'après Oscar Roty
obverse.lettering_translation: Republic of France 2011 Laurent Jorio after Oscar Roty

reverse.description: Geographic map of Europe with no internal borders with twelve vertical lines and stars to the left of denomination

comments:
Different Mint Master Marks
  • Hubert Lariviere, from 2007 to 2010, a mark of a hunting horn with a wave and a fish
  • Yves Sampo, since 2011 to 2020, a mark of a Pentagon with letters AG, MP and YS
  • Joaquin Jimenez, since 2021, a mark of a square with a circle and a broken line in the small square
